<!-- wp:group {"metadata":{"name":"Story"},"align":"full","className":"is-style-light-page-section","layout":{"type":"constrained"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignfull is-style-light-page-section"><!-- wp:columns {"align":"wide","style":{"spacing":{"blockGap":"var:preset|spacing|70"}}} -->
<div class="wp-block-columns alignwide"><!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"typography":{"lineHeight":"var:custom|line-height|body"}}} -->
<p style="line-height:var(--wp--custom--line-height--body)">Welcome to this special edition of your Wine Club, where we invite you to explore one of the world’s most influential wine styles through a distinctly South African lens: the Bordeaux blend. Rather than presenting a single finished wine, this edition takes a more immersive approach. Inside this box, you will find nine bottles, each showcasing a grape variety traditionally used in a Bordeaux blend. Tasted on their own, these wines reveal clarity and character; together, they demonstrate how South African winemakers create wines with balance, complexity and age-worthy structure — guided by both tradition and place. Originally developed in Bordeaux, France, this classic blend centres on Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot and Cabernet Franc, often supported by Petit Verdot, Malbec or Carménère. Each variety brings a specific strength — power, elegance, perfume, freshness or depth — and the art lies in blending these elements into something more complete and layered than any single grape alone.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"typography":{"lineHeight":"var:custom|line-height|body"}}} -->
<p style="line-height:var(--wp--custom--line-height--body)">Few places outside Bordeaux are as naturally suited to these varieties as South Africa. From Stellenbosch to Paarl, Franschhoek to the Cape South Coast, our diverse soils, abundant sunshine and cooling ocean influences allow these grapes to thrive. Over time, we have not simply replicated a European model — we have interpreted it, creating wines of confidence, character and unmistakable local expression. By sharing the components with you, we invite you to taste more intentionally — to explore how each element contributes to the whole and to deepen your appreciation for the craftsmanship behind every blend. Cheers to the Cape — and to great blends.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"typography":{"fontStyle":"italic","lineHeight":"var:custom|line-height|body"}},"textColor":"neutral-700","fontSize":"200"} -->
<p class="has-neutral-700-color has-text-color has-200-font-size" style="font-style:italic;line-height:var(--wp--custom--line-height--body)">Psst… Did you know? Bordeaux became a major winemaking region thanks to its historic port, a key export hub dating back to Roman Burdigala.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
